meta.description: Cathay Pacific First and Business Class Lounge at San Francisco International Airport (SFO), International Terminal A. Learn more about the lounge: amenities, photos, review, opening hours, location.

lounge.name: Cathay Pacific First and Business Class Lounge

location.terminalDirections: Immediately after security, turn left, proceed up the escalators and follow the signs

lounge.description: Welcome to the Cathay Pacific First and Business Class Lounge at SFO. Work or relax prior to your departure, and delight in the complimentary amenities, including shower facilities, iMacs, and the famed Noodle Bar.

reviews.content: A good oneworld lounge with plenty of space and an above average selection of food and drink. Shame itâ€™s tucked away in a corner as good views are limited.
One of the best lounges Iâ€™ve been to, only second to Icelandair in Reykjavik. The staff is top notch friendly. I canâ€™t wait to visit again.
This is a really great lounge with clean lines and delicious food.
Great alternative if flying Qantas to the AF/KLM lounge. Friendly staff, great food. Noodle Bar lives up to its rep.
A calm oasis. Entered as an AS Lounge member. Noodle bar just closed but substantial snacks available as well as a variety of wines. Great space.
Spacious but seriously lacking in good food or beverage. Noodle Bar is OK but otherwise no better than Admirals Club. Not what youâ€™d expect from a Cathay lounge.
Very nice lounge with variety of staying options, good food selection and nice work spaces.
This lounge is an excellent place to relax before your flight. Freshly made noodles are delicious and deli sandwiches are great. Solus chairs are available in the expanded area for extra comfort.
Great service, friendly Staff and a very relaxing time in this gorgeous lounge. Highly recommended.
Awesome lounge. One of the best at SFO. Real Chinese dishes and of course, the noodle bar. Plenty of space to spread out, plus showers and fast WiFi.
Really enjoyed this lounge. The food was delicious, and the coffee was strong. From a teammate, "the mocha tastes like candy." The WiFi could be a bit faster, but everything else was ðŸ‘Œ
Great views, food, and service!
What an excellent lounge! Great service, delicious premium food (make sure to try dan dan noodles soup!) and very comfortable seating area. 10/10!
On Alaska Airlines pass. They kicked me out of one area that was Cathay Pacific only (no signs, no explanation). Several loud announcements of the Cathay Pacific flights over PA and individually.
Being a Qantas Platinum wasn't allowed access for some reason, been here many times before.
As a British Airways passenger, this lounge was a welcome escape from the crowds over at the BA lounges. Food selection was alright but there was a delicious noodle bar. Spacious, clean, and modern.
Outstanding lounge on West Coast. Alaska Board Room grants access. Good food selection and great liquors. Got here and no one around since Hong Kong flight boards are 1:10.
A typical Cathay quality lounge. Great place to go before your flight. Modern design, comfortable seating, showers, wifi. Much better than domestic lounges in the US.
Nice lounge for AS customers.
One of the best lounges at SFO.
Area is small, facility tends to be old.

Simple yet efficient and Comfortable lounge. Small enough to be cozy and big enough to have enough space. Like the view of tarmac/planes. Food is healthy and tasty. Overall a quiet refuge at busy SFO.
Nice and clean with plenty of wiring space.
Very convenient if a little tricky to find.
Gives you a feeling of back home to Hong Kong.
Thank goodness for the Cathay Lounge at SFO!! It made my 4 hour layover fly by!
The food is good, the beer is good, and the staff keeps you in good spirits.
Nice and pleasant during Saturday afternoon.
Awesome lounge - awesome noodle bar - great experience!
Fantastic clam chowder & fresh sour dough bread, fruits are fresh but coffee machine not too good. Friendly staff & quiet ambience. Lounge set up similar to other Cathay lounges worldwide.
I get to the airport a little early just to be able to relax and have a nice light dinner before my flight..Excellent!
Noodle bar is great. The buffet options are good too. This is a mixed biz/first lounge. Can get a tad crowded but you'll always enjoy space. Good amount of media as well.
So excited to find out they accept Alaska Airlines Board Room Members! It was after 2pm when I entered so they had stopped serving any lunch, but I was happy with a glass of wine and snacks!
#CathayPacificSFO. Lounge is fantastic. Fabulous stsff, very friendly.
Very nice lounge with great snacks!
Great lounge, can get busy. Can't wait to see the place after expansion is finished.
Amazing and very pleased.  Would definitely come back.
Great lounge!  Everything is great....except the dandan noodle is not good, not up to the HKG lounge standard.
Decent food, nice bathrooms, helpful and courteous staff!
So clean and pretty. Though crowded, it's relaxing. A good stop if you have time to kill.

A great place to grab a comfy seat, a cold drink, and some tasty noodles before boarding the long-haul flight to HKG. Looks like they are expanding their facility to better serve the 2 red eye flights.
Wonderful lounge but limited food when a Cathay Pacific flight is not scheduled.
I have been to many lounges and The Cathay lounge is extraordinary. The best treat was the Hong Kong Noodle Soup. Really authentic Hong Kong taste. The staff were amazing too.
Awesome! Especially the wonton noodles.
Staffs are very helpful and attentive.  Foods are ok.
Food is ok. Wine and beverages are great. Quite and clean.
Clean and tidy lounge. Good Asian food.
Excellent lounge. Stopped by en route to Seattle on Alaska Airlines, and the staff was very courteous. The lounge is clean with decent food selection (Asian and Western choices).
Went before Alaska flight to Seattle.  Self service wine and liquor were top notch.    Was there in the evening so noodle bar was shut down.  Great seating and very private when I was there.
I have used the lounge twice while traveling on early flights to Seattle on AK Airlines. The staff are very friendly, hospitable and professional. All of the amenities make this a 1st Class Lounge.
Busy but nice. A big improvement over Delta's Sky Club. Great breakfast, self pour drinks, and a noodle bar :-)
Average lounge that can get crowded.  Food is essentially self service and average.  Noodle bar has 3 options. I was not disappointed by the food but not wowed either. Liquor is self serve (good).
This is the typical Cathay Lounge. One word: Amazing.
This is a great lounge with comfortable seats and an excellent noodle bar.
This is a wonderful place to hang before your flight. The lounge has an awesome noodle bar, comfy chairs, new Apple computers, decent self-serve bar, and great decor.

location.terminalDirections: Concourse A, Level 3. Take the first left after the TSA Checkpoint and the lounge is located straight ahead.
Pier A Departures Concourse, Level 3, near Gate A5
Immediately after security, turn left and proceed up the escalators to the entrance on Level 4.
Concourse A, Level 4. Take the first left after the TSA Checkpoint and go up the escalators.
Immediately after security, turn left, proceed up the escalators and follow the signs
Boarding Area A, Level 3, between Gates A2 and A6
After security, turn left and take the lift to Level 5.
